routing_summary.excerpt_summary: Section 8 is an acknowledgments section that credits individuals and notes prior RFCs used as models for TLS usage, TLS resumption, and PSK recommendations.

Temporal.explanation: No sequencing, timers, or state transitions are specified here.

ActorDirectionality.explanation: Only general acknowledgments; no sender/receiver roles or behaviors are defined.

Scope.explanation: No normative rules whose scope could be misapplied; just descriptive text.

Causal.explanation: No cause-effect protocol behavior is described; nothing implementable depends on this section.

Quantitative.explanation: No numeric limits, sizes, or ranges are given.

Deontic.explanation: No RFC 2119 keywords or normative requirements appear here.

Structural.explanation: No ABNF, YANG, diagrams, or field formats are present.

CrossRFC.explanation: Other RFCs are only mentioned as sources of inspiration in acknowledgments; minor inaccuracies here would not affect interoperability.

Terminology.explanation: Only informal descriptive terms; no protocol terminology is defined or constrained.

Boundary.explanation: No edge cases or exceptional behaviors are discussed.
